SmControl

Class SmProduct

  • java.lang.Object
    • SmControl.SmProduct

  • public class SmProduct
extends java.lang.Object
    This class handles the writing of products out to their files and the creation of the directory structure for the automated prism code. This class assumes a file name structure for the V0 files.

        public java.lang.String[] writeOutProducts(java.lang.String inDir)
                                    throws java.io.IOException
        Writes out each of the products to the respective folder, first creating the full path name, then writing out the text file, then adding the name of the file to the log list.
        Parameters:
        inDir - not used here
        Returns:
        the text file list of file names (log list)
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if unable to write out the file

      • buildFilename

        public java.nio.file.Path buildFilename(java.io.File outloc,
                                        java.lang.String localdir,
                                        java.lang.String fileName,
                                        java.lang.String fileExtension,
                                        java.lang.String channel,
                                        java.lang.String ext)
        Builds the output filename from a folder path, file name, file extension, channel number, and V2 processing type extension
        Parameters:
        outloc - the output folder for this file
        localdir - the directory for the specific cosmos file type
        fileName - the file name
        fileExtension - the extension of V1, V2, etc.
        channel - the channel id if needed in the filename
        ext - an extension for V2s, such as 'acc', 'vel', or 'dis'
        Returns:
        the full file path

      • deleteV0AfterProcessing

        public void deleteV0AfterProcessing(java.io.File source)
                             throws java.io.IOException
        Removes the input file from the input directory, if it exists, and if the Delete Input Files flag in the configuration file is set to 'Yes'. If the configuration file is set to 'No', the file is not deleted.
        Parameters:
        source - the input file
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if unable to delete the file

      • buildTroubleLog

        public java.lang.String[] buildTroubleLog(java.lang.String[] inlog)
        Builds a trouble log from the list of all log files. If there are no files going to trouble folders, the list returned has size 0.
        Parameters:
        inlog - the list of all output files
        Returns:
        a list of output files going to trouble folders, or a list of length 0 if no trouble files found.

      • setDirectories

        public void setDirectories(java.lang.String rcid,
                           java.lang.String scnlauth,
                           java.lang.String eventMarker,
                           VFileConstants.V2Status V2result)
        Method to set up the directory structure within the output directory.
        Parameters:
        rcid - extracted from the input file, this defines the folder structure according to the SCNL code
        scnlauth - must be present in the V0 for the standard folder structure to be put in place.
        eventMarker - event time pulled from the file header in case of Orphan, this event time will be used in place of the station name
        V2result - flag for the creation of a Trouble folder
